Grep and Find Commands for DevOps

These are some of the most commonly used search commands during DevOps work. Every command below includes what it does and when we use it.

Grep Commands

grep "word" filename
Searches for a word in a file.

grep -n "word" filename
Displays matching lines along with line numbers.

grep -c "word" filename
Displays count of matching lines.

grep -i "word" filename
Searches ignoring case (case-insensitive).

grep -v "word" filename
Displays lines that do NOT contain the word.

grep -e "w1" -e "w2" -e "w3" filename
Searches for multiple words in a file.

grep "w1" file1 file2
Searches a word in multiple files.

grep -e "w1" -e "w2" -e "w3" file1 file2
Searches multiple words in multiple files.

grep -r "word" .
Searches recursively in current directory.

grep -rn "word" .
Recursive search with line numbers.

grep -l "word" filename
Displays only file names containing the word.

grep -w "word" filename
Matches exact word only.

grep -o "word" filename
Displays only matched word.

grep --color "word" filename
Highlights matching text.

Find Commands

find . -name file1
Finds file named file1 in current directory.

find /etc -name passwd
Finds passwd file inside /etc directory.

find . -user username
Finds files owned by a user.

find . -group groupname
Finds files belonging to a group.

find . -perm 777
Finds files with 777 permissions.

find . -type f
Finds only files.

find . -type d
Finds only directories.

find . -size +10M
Finds files greater than 10MB.

find . -size -1M
Finds files less than 1MB.

find . -empty
Finds empty files and folders.

find . -mtime -1
Finds files modified in last 1 day.

find . -exec rm -rf {} ;
Deletes found files (use carefully).

Locate Command

locate filename
Finds file quickly using database.

updatedb
Updates locate database.

Important Notes

grep is used for searching content inside files
find is used for searching files and directories
locate is faster but depends on database
use -r in grep for recursive search
use find carefully when deleting files
permissions and ownership can be filtered using find

